<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000008#    01#        66.10#">Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-66.10</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_8.01-66.10"/><heading><desig>§ 8.01-66.10.</desig><title>Death claims settled by compromise or suit</title></heading><bodyText><p>In case of personal injuries resulting in death and settlement therefor by compromise or suit under the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-50"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-50">§§ 8.01-50<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#           50#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 8.01-56"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 8.01-56">8.01-56<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000008#    01#           56#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, the liens provided for in this article may be asserted against the recovery, or against the estate of the decedent, but not both. If asserted against the recovery and paid, such liens shall attach pro rata to the amounts received respectively by such beneficiaries as are designated to receive the moneys distributed and in their respective amounts; and such beneficiaries, or the personal representative for their benefit, shall be subrogated to the liens against the estate of such decedent provided for by <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-528"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-528">§ 64.2-528<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#          528#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 32-141; 1979, c. 722.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PSB0-004G-K09N-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 8.01.</desig><title>CIVIL REMEDIES AND PROCEDURE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 3.</desig><title>ACTIONS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 7.1.</desig><title>LIEN FOR HOSPITAL, MEDICAL AND NURSING SERVICES</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classificationGroup classificationScheme="indexing-terms"><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Insurance Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MDM4MzQ2QUYzMTY0NDQzQTkxRDQwRUUzRUM5RDg0OEM7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem score="50"><className>Liens &amp; Subrogation</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6Q0M1MkU4QTA1RDRCNDc0MkE1RUI3QkQ2NjNFMzVCNzA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MjYxQTRCQ0ZCNjgyNDg5Nzk4OTA5OTI3Q0Q3M0FFNjc</classCode></classificationItem></classificationIte